Description.
Male (
Holotype
, Amazonas, 
Brazil
, MNHN). Total length 15.42. Carapace 7.84 long, 7.71 wide, light brown with a broad lateral band of white setae; live specimens present a dark green colouration (
Fig. 6
). Clypeus light brown with a median patch of white setae, 1.06 high. Anterior eye row slightly procurved (
Fig. 11
), 1.40 wide; posterior recurved, 2.44 wide. Eye diameters, interdistances, and median ocular quadrangle: AME 0.22, ALE 0.14, PME 0.30, PLE 0.32; AME-AME 0.28, AME-ALE 0.18, PME-PME 0.48, PME-PLE 0.50, OQA 0.80, OQP 1.10, OQH 0.68. Chelicerae dark brown, divergent, with a lateral depression; covered with scattered setae (
Fig. 11
). Sternum light brown, darker laterally, bristly; 3.32 long, 3.85 wide. Labium dark brown, lighter distally, 1.19 long, 1.10 wide. Legs light brown, unmarked, relative length: IV-II-I-III, I—femur 8.77/ patella-tibia 12.10/ metatarsus 7.04/ tarsus 3.85/ total 31.76; II—8.91/ 12.23/ 7.31/ 3.72/ 32.17; III—8.24/ 10.77/ 6.95/ 2.66/ 28.62; IV—9.97/ 13.03/ 8.91/ 4.78/ 36.69. Ventral pairs of macrosetae on tibiae: I-4; II-4; III-4; IV-4. Abdomen 5.71 long, dark green with several white spots on dorsum, bristly; with two pairs of sigillae. Venter light brown, bristly. Palpus with a small median apophysis with two rounded tips (
Fig. 57
); DTP elongated (
Fig. 56
). Ectal branch of RTA with a small lamellar projection at the base (
Fig. 59
) and ental branch of RTA with a well developed lamellar base and a short and ventrally curved tip (
Figs 58, 59
).

Female (Santarém, Pará, 
Brazil
, MNHN). Total length 15.02. Carapace 7.31 long, 6.78 wide, colour as in male. Clypeus as in male, 0.82 high. Anterior eye row straight, 1.42 wide; posterior recurved, 2.20 wide. Eye diameters, interdistances, and median ocular quadrangle: AME 0.22, ALE 0.18, PME 0.30, PLE 0.32; AME-AME 0.26, AME-ALE 0.20, PME-PME 0.44, PME-PLE 0.54, OQA 0.76, OQP 1.02, OQH 0.84. Chelicerae light brown, bristly. Sternum as in male, with scattered setae; 3.32 long, 3.45 wide. Labium dark brown, 1.06 long, 1.33 wide. Legs as in male, relative length: IV-II-I-III, I—femur 8.24/ patella-tibia 10.90/ metatarsus 6.65/ tarsus 3.32/ total 29.11; II—8.77/ 11.30/ 6.78/ 3.72/ 30.57; III—7.98/ 9.70/ 6.63/ 3.05/ 27.36; IV—9.97/ 12.23/ 9.31/ 4.78/ 36.29. Ventral pairs of macrosetae on tibiae: I-4; II-5; III-3; IV-3. Tarsal organ slightly elliptical (
Fig. 65
), positioned on the third half of tarsus (
Fig. 64
). Base of trichobothria with a smooth hood (
Fig. 63
). Superior tarsal claw with eight teeth (
Fig. 66
) and inferior with one tooth (
Fig. 67
). Abdomen 8.37 long, colour as in male. Epigynum with a laterally excavated middle field, with conspicuous lateral lobes (
Fig. 60
). Copulatory duct (CD1) membranous and CD2 sclerotized and with a rounded border (
Fig. 61
); head of spermathecae with very distinct and large pores (
Fig. 62
).
